insect_info.name: Honeybee
insect_info.features: striped abdomen, transparent wings, pollen baskets on legs, detailed antennae

prompt:
Create exactly one single Honeybee (Apis mellifera) in vintage scientific illustration style. 
        Key requirements:
        1. Child-friendly appearance while maintaining scientific accuracy
        2. Clear, clean lines with educational value
        3. Precise anatomical details but not scary or intimidating
        4. Use precise fine black ink lines to define form and structure
        5. Apply subtle golden brown and black watercolor washes
        6. Position in side-dorsal view showing standing position showing body structure
        7. Show detailed features: striped abdomen, transparent wings, pollen baskets on legs, detailed antennae
        8. Pure white background
        9. Match the style of 19th century scientific illustration
        10. Ensure the entire insect is visible
        
        Style reference: Classic natural history illustration with educational focus.
